
Event Chatbot Project

Overview

This project is an AI-powered event recommendation chatbot that helps users find events based on their preferences and notifies them about upcoming events via WhatsApp and Telegram. It includes:

A trained LLM for event recommendations (LangChain + OpenAI)

WhatsApp and Telegram chatbot integration

A web page displaying dynamic event listings

Automated event notifications

Features

Users can interact with the chatbot via WhatsApp or Telegram to find events.

AI-powered event selection based on user preferences.

Automatic notifications for relevant upcoming events.

A web interface displaying event details dynamically.

Tech Stack

Backend: Python (Flask), SQLite

Frontend: React.js

AI: LangChain, OpenAI Embeddings

Messaging: Twilio API (WhatsApp), Telegram Bot API

Data: Event scraping (Eventbrite API)

Installation & Setup

1. Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-repo/event-chatbot.git
cd event-chatbot

2. Set up Python backend:

cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py

3. Set up React frontend:

cd frontend
npm install
npm start

4. Set up environment variables:

Create a .env file and add:

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_key
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_token
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=your_twilio_sid
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your_twilio_auth_token
EVENTBRITE_API_KEY=your_eventbrite_api_key

How to Use

Start the backend (python app.py)

Start the frontend (npm start)

Use the Telegram bot or WhatsApp bot to request event recommendations.

Open http://localhost:3000 to see the event listings.

Future Improvements

Add more event filtering options (category, date, location).

Store user preferences for personalized recommendations.

Improve UI with event search and filters.

